narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: This semester, I not only learned about certain calculus topics (like the chain rule, integrals, and differential equations) but more importantly, I learned about their real-life applications.

I learned how to integrate, find solutions to differential equations and solve related rate questions. I also learned how to apply various concepts to the same question and how to see the real life application for things like modeling through differential equations.
I developed more skills in calculus.
Concluded the mastering of calculus: derivatives, limits, integrals

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: The ULA's and professors have many office hours and they are more than willing to help you understand topics and walk through problems.

The course content is very comprehensive and there is a lot of study material that is offered before exams. The ULAs are also really wonderful! I don't think there are any weaknesses of this course that stand out to me.

Huge weakness is not preparing students well for the exams. I felt going to class was pointless because it did not help. 

Biggest strengths are the ULA's. Would not have passed the class without their help.

The only weaknesses I encountered with this course was the scheduling of office hours for the ULA's. They would typically be around 7 pm to 10 pm, which was hard as a student-athlete who had other obligations and needed to also ensure getting enough sleep to perform well in all my classes.

Strengths: Bobby was very engaged and an awesome professor who explains things very clearly with ample examples. 
Weaknesses: Organization of course. Very confusing to know what was due and was not due to changing due dates and deadlines.
The peer tutors were the strongest aspect of this course. They were incredibly helpful, patient, and knowledgeable. Sometimes, I felt like I learned more from them than my instructors.
Classes dont help learn the psets only the office hours do

I think that the textbook used in this course was very helpful as well as the psets used to guide the learning in the course however I think that some of the exams could be more similar to the practice exams provided.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Yes, although I don't know what Math 112 looks like I feel that Math 110/111 provides you with a strong foundation for future math courses. The sequence does a good job at introducing new calculus topics and relating them to past knowledge (like pre-cal)
Yes I would! It was really helpful in building my foundation of calculus and doing so in a way that is well rounded.
It was hard for me so i wouldnt
Yes I would, I think that this is a better pace to learn math concepts completely
